react is a library of javascript
component based model
reusibility (declarative approach)

for installing first time react in pc--------->

* npm install --global create-react-app

for checking version of react app-->
* create-react-app --version

d: for change localdisk in cmd


for creating react app --> 
* create-react-app projectname


***package.json 
me hamre project ke information hoti ha sariii
react ki configuration hote ha
isme jo library hum use kar rhe hote  wo check kar sakte ha
package.json used to store the metadata associated with the project as well as to store
list of dependency packages 
isme wo packages jo nodemodules me safe haa

package-lock.json me logs bante ha not a important file you can delete it (waste file)


for host page in github 
use this link --> https://create-react-app.dev/docs/deployment/
and watch this video-->https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mdO18zv3oGQ

SPA=>single Page Application
MPA=>Multiple Page Application

another setup for  without installing create reactapp is
npx create-react-app project name

React ko server par hi chala sakte ha like:localhost....


public 
index.html ke andar
 id=>root ke andar hamari poori application chal rhi hoti ha

